# JavaScript Modules

Vanilla ES modules only. No bundler, no npm packages.

## Architecture

- `site/js/core/eventbus.js` — pub/sub between components (`emit`, `on`)
- `site/js/core/progress.js` — localStorage progress (`intuitive:progress:<topic-id>`)
- `site/js/core/router.js` — scroll-spy section navigation (IntersectionObserver)
- `site/js/components/` — quiz, pipeline-viz, tab-panel, comparison, etc.
- `site/js/topics/registry.js` — single source of truth for topics and reading order

## Progress and quiz flow

1. Quiz completes → `emit('quiz:passed', { conceptSlug })`
2. `progress.js` listens and writes to localStorage
3. Progress ring reads from same topic id as registry

## Common pitfalls

- Topic id case mismatch across registry, `data-progress-ring`, and `initProgress()`
- Quiz score must use `>= 0.75` (float), not `>= 75` (integer division)
- `data-viz-type` must match a handler in `pipeline-viz.js`
- Comparison slider needs `{ passive: false }` and `preventDefault()` on pointermove

## Data files

- Naming: `<concept-slug>-data.js` in `site/js/topics/<topic>/`
- Export `quiz` array and viz config (`stages`, `comparison`, etc.)
